{{Speciesbox | taxon = Gobius senegambiensis | authority = [[Jan Marie Metzelaar|Metzelaar]], 1919 }}
'''''Gobius senegambiensis''''' is a species of [[goby]] native to the [[Atlantic Ocean]] from [[Morocco]] to [[Angola]] as well as the islands in the [[Gulf of Guinea]] where it is found in [[inshore]] waters on sandy substrates. This species can reach a length of {{convert|7.3|cm|in}} [[fish measurement|SL]].<ref>{{FishBase |genus= Gobius|species= senegambiensis| month = June | year = 2013}}</ref>
The species is named after where they were described in one location, [[Senegambia]], a region compromising [[Senegal]] and the [[Gambia]].
