{{notability|date=June 2011}}

The '''Weather Information Exchange Model''' (WXXM) is a platform that was originally designed by [[Eurocontrol|EUROCONTROL]] for the exchange of [[weather]] related information between users.<ref>http://www.eurocontrol.int/aim/public/standard_page/met_wie.html</ref>

It is now a proposed standard of the [[Open Geospatial Consortium|Open Geospatial Consortium (OGC)]] and is used by both Eurocontrol and the [[Federal Aviation Administration|FAA]].<ref>http://www.opengeospatial.org/domain/aviation</ref><ref>http://www.aixm.aero/public/standard_page/2010_05_aixm_met.html</ref>

